caption: I let our server decide what I got. She chose the orecchiette with sausage and asparagus, and a Hello Again cocktail (something like a fancy margarita.) Both were very good and very well made. I would recommend this spot for sure!

Absolutely disappointed on the service. Half an hour in after we sat down, I had to alert the waitress at the entrance that no server had come to our table to even provide us tap water or at the very least, say hello. Michael, who didn’t even apologized, served us with a horrible attitude, extremely unorganized and uninterested in serving us and make sure we had a pleasant time. Is not the first time I’ve been to Ainslie but it was my first time seating inside, the place is beautiful and the vibes are cozy which I love, but the service needs to be improved significantly. Otherwise is not worth the visit, there are plenty of other restaurants that main focus is to provide a better service and a server that is fully dedicated to provide the best hospitality
Great food and excellent service!

One our favorite (go-to) restaurants in Brooklyn. Very appreciative of Luke for getting us a table when the place was packed. Staff is great and ambience is perfect. Food is on point too! Will keep coming back..
Been there twice. Poor customer service. Food comes out too quickly and is so-so. Okay drink selection. Only thing special is a nice atmosphere.
The aesthetic is to die for. Had a group for a birthday brunch. Had plenty of mimosas. Worth the price with the atmosphere. All around amazing time.

So pretty!!! Great setting for a date - felt like that sweet spot of being a nice place for a date but also felt casual. Food was decent. Wait staff wasn’t the friendliest when I went but I will contribute that towards Covid stress.
Won’t come again for dinner. When all courses come out 5m after ordering, and are lukewarm, somethings amiss. Gross ribs, inedible cauliflower, salad with too much dressing. Weak spot.

Place is great! Inside is beautiful.Drinks are very good but food not so great.Pasta simple no cheese on the top,pizza just simple nothing special.I ordered with spicy sausage not spicy at all and thick slices, is Italian place and I feel like this Italian kitchen runs Mexican people who prepare the food for this prices food should be better quality.
Superb fun as an outdoor space. We did a large group and they were very accommodating.  As a heads up for larger groups it is a set menu - not at all a bad thing though!!

Nice atmosphere, lots of space, make a reservation for no wait and seating. The customer service was great, she was on top of everything and was very fast. Food is good and served quickly. Will definitely visit again 👌🏾
Very nice place had a great meal there.

A cool spot for friends or a date. It's huge! Plus there is outdoor dining as well. What did we try? The steak and mashed potatoes, the pizza, calamari, Brussel sprouts,  the Spaghetti dish, tiramisu and of course drinks.  Everything was great!! We visited on a Sunday evening.  Parking was the only challenge.  Service was good. There is a 90 minute limit but if you are ordering, they do not seem to rush you. This place is a must try in Williamsburg.

Went for bottomless brunch and our server never came back to our table to refill our carafe. When we finally got her attention she told us she would only give us one refill since we only had 20 minutes left of bottomless.. basically wasnt bottomless because we indeed reached the bottom and were sitting there for like 45 minutes with empty glasses

Best brunch spot! This place is huge and beautiful. The back patio is covered and warm, inside is airy and spacious and everything is tastefully designed and decorated. The food is great! I love their eggs in purgatory and the breakfast pizza, but staple brunch items are also on point. They have a bottomless brunch that I haven't been brave enough to try, but drinks I have had there were good.

Management was so poor. The hostess Diane had an incredibly rude and condescending attitude because we arrived ten minutes late. It was actually hilarious and kinda sad to see this girl treat customers with such hostility just to go on some power trip.  Food and drinks were great though and our server was really good, but this girls attitude really gave the whole place a bad look overall. No one wants to give their money to a business that thinks they’re better than their customers.
Great wait service, beautiful outdoor space!

Best brunch deal in Williamsburg! The food is delicious Italian fare, with pasta and pizza being a mainstay. There’s also pancakes, shakshuka, and eggs. My boyfriend always opts for the Steak and Eggs, while I opt for the sweeter selection.  I wasn’t a fan of the Bloody Mary here, but the spiked iced tea is delicious and so is the mimosa.  I wanted to sit in the outdoor garden, but was told that it’s reserved for bigger parties 8-10.  If you’re organizing a large breakfast party or want to get a little tipsy on the weekend with your SO, this is the spot!!  Plant based options? There’s plenty of vegetable side dishes and salads to accommodate any vegan or plant based diet?

We had a superb brunch at Ainslie! We loved the food (we had “eggs in purgatory”, which were eggs baked in a spicy tomato sauce & creamy polenta, spaghetti cacio e pepe and eggs Benedict), and the unlimited brunch cocktails (for 90 mins) were poured very generously. The restaurant itself has a fantastic decor and a really cool vibe, great for group outings. Looking forward to trying their dinner menu next.
My server was so sweet very friendly. My first time there, I would definitely come back because, of him.
Very nice atmosphere. Food is reasonable priced and tasty. Drinks can be stronger.
This is one of the best places I have been to. I highly suggest it.
Went for my birthday brunch and loved it! Best bottomless brunch deal out there!!!
Nice place, good food a bit pricey but well worth it. Must see.
I went here for the first time on my birthday and they made it special for me. The place is great. Has a nice atmosphere and vibe. The food and drinks are amazing!
Bad service. Overpriced food. Watery drinks. If you go with a group they force you to get a family style meal that is overpriced penne.
Had a delicious outdoor brunch with the girls. The space is huge, the outdoor dining is huge and the French toast is even huger! 🖤
Great Service and dope scenery
This place is a hidden gem in Brooklyn. The ambiance is amazing and their small plates are delicious. Totally recommend their arancini, Margherita pizza small plates and prosecco!

Good cocktails and food but very overpriced. Check before you specify your liquor brand, they added a 6 dollar extra for Woodford Reserve on top of the $14 cocktail price and it came out to $20. And the server was very aggressive about rushing us to order the main course even though there were a lot of tables empty so no reason to rush us so much. A place more fitting to be in Manhattan than Williamsburg.
Very good food and cocktails but the service is poor.
Love the ambience Food is super average

I had a spectacular night tonight with my girlfriend and mom. We all loved it and the experience was heightened by the phenomenal staff there. Tanya and George were great! I can’t wait to go back and I encourage anyone reading this to go have dinner there and be stunned

I crave this lasagna all the time now and that fusilli pasta *chefs kiss*. Split a pizza because we couldn’t help ourselves but omg was it worth it! Definitely will be coming back! Check out IG- newyorkcitymunchies for more 📸
Very nice place and food ! They drinks where not the best , the attention was good but they kick us out because an other reservation , they let us stay just for one hour and a half

Awesome order from Ainslie.  Superb.  Can’t decide which item is best.  Charred wood fired wings, crispy but still tender - terrific Gorgonzola dipping sauce (an Italian nod and a wink to Buffalo). Tender falloff the bone country style ribs, subtly seasoned Italian style.  Melt in your mouth meatballs in tomato sauce.  Can’t emphasize how they have mastered that important balance between meat and bread crumbs that creates something so soft and delicious.   Perfect broccoli rabe, just a touch of bitterness but not too much.  Roasted potatoes, crispy.  Love the Italian riff on BBQ,  could eat this all day long without that greasy nasty over full feeling you get sometimes from American bbq.  Here’s the wing in Gorgonzola. Plus, all of this traveled from Williamsburg to boerum hill (20+ minutes) really well.  Didn’t skip a beat.  Bravo!
My girlfriends and I went for brunch a few weeks ago and had such a amazing time! The food was fantastic and our server Cat was just one of the nicest and attentive servers my friends and I ever had.
Italian food in large outdoor heated structure. The burger was super gooey with Gorgonzola. Tables are nicely spaced out. There’s also a large heated backyard space that’s pretty with green plants.
Best wood burning Pizza I had in a long time
Beautiful converted space with Italian family style fixings and outdoor beer garden.
Cute outdoor set up with heat lamps and great service

The House Made Lasagna and Arancini were great, but the pizza was pretty much flavorless which is disappointing for an Italian restaurant. The tiramisu was alright, but I’ve had better. The service was pretty good but this is not a restaurant at the top of my list to return to.
Food was very good, ambiance on point. In between our appetizer and salad (we did family style) we had to practically beg for new plates, which was odd. But otherwise, I would recommend.
Great beer garden vibe in the back. Their hanger steak was delicious and great service!
Good outdoor seating with great social distancing measures. Also the food and drinks are top notch.
Great food, very fast service - exactly what’s needed for a perfect winter outdoor dining experience!
This experience was really nice. Family style dining was great.
Great atmosphere! By far my favorite place in New York. In my next visit, I'll make a point to eat here.  Staff was awesome and extremely attentive.  The family style meal was also nice!
Amazing place to spend time with friends. Good food. Great ambience.

Brunch food was disappointing. They have so much potential but need to figure it out in the kitchen. Not one of the four entries we had was good. Very bad eggs Benedict. On the other entires they pretty much served a full plate of beets. Gross.
The food was good but we need to give it another try during non-covid. We were rushed out after one hour and the food came instantly upon ordering.  It’s expensive but ... expected?
Met up with some friends i hadn't seen since start of quarantine. They have ample space to maintain social distancing even when indoors. The hangar steak was delish.
Food is absolutely amazing the ambience the people that work there you will not be disappointed and the food quality is awesome

Question: How much wood would a wood chuck chuck if a wood chuck could eat seaford linguini, mild dry rub spiced wings, risotto balls, two glasses of a copper legend lager, and some spare slices of bread?  Answer: Not much! Cause after eating that meal there is nothing more the chuck would want. The dining experience completed every aspect of my life and if I were to die now, there's not much that I would regret missing out on.
A lovely restaurant and great spot for bottomless brunch and a variety of brunch food!

this is the worst place i’ve been to for brunch in williamsburg. they have tiny atrocious stools and someone fell off of one and instead of making sure they were ok they immediately took away the drinks we paid for and told us we had to leave. they have horrible customer service and clearly do not care about their business. I was appalled at the low level of standards they upheld and would not recommend anyone going here for brunch.

Beautiful ambiance and spacious restaurant. Definitely not the most welcoming or accommodating place for a big group even with COVID regulations in place. We came here for brunch on Saturday November 7th. The food was family style which we liked and the drinks were amazing. Our waitress Jackie was the highlight of our experience. She went above & beyond for our party of 14. Her attitude, attentiveness, communication, patience was 10/10. Unfortunately, it wasn’t the most positive time in the beginning and the manager knows why BUT Jackie made it a wonderful experience overall and everyone in our party loved her service. thanks so much Jackie, this business is fortunate to have you!
Perfect back garden
Love this place! Would come back for brunch time and time again. The bottomless breakfast is so worth it!
I love this place
Food was delicious

A birthday  dinner ruined, I would like to say first and foremost the service and server was incredible. Unfortunately the management and host staff were incredibly disappointing. We were told several  times that 10 guests could be accommodated and because  of this information I booked  my bday dinner at this restaurant. It seemed  perfect  but we were brought  to a table that only sat 6 people  and the host and management continued to throw up every  bad covid excuse on why they couldn't  seat us. They kept insisting that we all sit down  because we were not distancing ourselves from the other guests at a different table . I kept explaining their wasnt anywhere for us to sit and were they expecting us to try to fit 8 people  at a table set for 6. They kept telling  us that they could add seats to the ends of the table but Clearly there was a break down in communication because  no one added a seat. I offered up suggestions  to split the table and was was told no ultimately 2 friends  walked out after being made to feel so unwelcome. Management switch  us to a table  for 10 and we sat and ate with empty seats where our friends could have been.

I've been wanted to come here for a few months. Finally I convinced my husband and we made a reservation. We decided to sit inside since indoor dining has begun. The ambiance is so pretty. You can come here for a drink with the girls/guys but you can also come here for a date night. Food is amazing! We had the wings and burata for apps. Both wonderful! I had the burger- (the prosciutto is not cooked) it was so yummy and cooked perfectly. My husband had one of the pizzas- also great.  For drinks he had the ocean ave and I had a non-alcoholic cider!  Everything was perfect. Can't wait to return for brunch!

My friend and I went for her birthday we were a party of eight and a reservation for 8 o’clock and we were seated at 8:30 and we didn’t leave the restaurant until three hours later we didn’t receive our drinks and most of our food came either late or cold we complained many times but nothing was done about it until the very last moment when we were leaving and got tired of waiting
Great place,  great food!
Great
Great ambience! The pastas were pretty average. Delicious cocktails
The decor the food the drinks the whole vibe, love it!

honestly the best brunch deal and fries in the hood in COVID times. Good safety and health measures in place while maintaining great service. Love the QR menu and ordering system where you pay when you order -- pls keep this going forward!
Very good food and service is great totally recommend
Big open backyard and a great bottomless brunch price
Awesome food and drink..didnt have a reservation...just walking by and they accommodated us

Came in on a rainy day and was not disappointed! Had the Chicken Milanese over tomato salad. Wasn't disappointed with it! Overall the ambiance was amazing when its the evening! Forgot to take a picture of my dish individually <I was hungry>
They seated us in the direct sun, but brunch pre fix food was good!

I loved my visit to Ainslie this past weekend. The back patio is beautiful and very spacious. The mobile ordering system is fast, easy, and minimized person-to-person contact, very nice given our current climate. And finally, and most importantly, the food was delicious, and somehow priced very reasonably!
The service excellent, the food awesome and delicious. The ambient  reminiscent of a garden Vila. Love it, I highly recommend it ❤️

Loved the ambiance of this space, and the food was tasty and full of flavor! The process of paying for our food was great, allowed my girlfriend and I to do things seamlessly while there.  I see myself returning again.

If you’re going to come here it’s surely going to be for the atmosphere and the drinks which are great. This place offers a unique dining experience with mostly communal type seating which is great for large groups. Now who ever manned the door last Wednesday night needs never to do so ever again( two middle aged men).  My group of 8 stood outside for a good 5 min and no one offered assistance or acknowledged our presence. If you’re thinking of dining here I recommend going family style and sharing. We ordered many different items from the menu and overall the food was ok. Most items which are labeled wood fired like the beets and wings do not evoke any Smokey or wood fired flavors. The Hanger steak was cooked well and rested but was ice cold when served to me. I’m not a big Neapolitan pizza type of guy but I know a good pie when I taste one and the prosciutto/sage pie was disappointing and uneventful. The margarita pie was decent. Now they do have what seems to be a traditional Stefano Ferrara oven Which is a plus but the pies we had that night did not excite. No complaints on service at the table. Our server was attentive and energetic and the busboys were courteous and efficient.

I had an enormous desire to bring my wife to Ainslie. I would drive by everyday and was astonish by their decor, however because of Covid-19, things had to be pause. It was my birthday and the first choice in my mind was Ainslie, boy I will REGRET it later. As we arrived the manager didn’t even greet us and for some reason made us seat at a table that was not of our desire ( to close to other people). According to him that’s was the only table available, mind you the restaurant was empty. As other guest arrived they were able to pick their table of choice, ok fine that was ODD. We order our food and drinks, to be fair their drinks were pretty good but the food was not at all. My steak was dry and chewy and my wife’s pork was uncooked. To keep this short I will never go back to Ainslie, I regret picking this spot, the greeter or manager should be change, horrible way to make a first impression.

Very romantic with youthful flair,music was fun,ambiance, during this very difficult time with Covid ,masks...they really stepped up and make you feel like it's a safe place to go out and have a good night! Air flowing,space,dividers between seating! Food was so good! You basically order for yourself and pay for it...then the food and drinks come. Not much for service or direction at this time,we wanted more drinks but couldnt do it in the app and there was no one to ask...you pretty much scan the menu and go through your order yourself,log in and purchase on your phone which is great during these trying times but getting advice, etc on menu ..didn't happen. Drinks and food came fast! Calamari so good! pizza , steak and cosmos!! Mmmm!! We will be back!
Don't have a great selection of beers.
Delicious food ...good service 😊😊😊

This is truly a hidden gem in NYC. Totally didn’t expect this place to be so beautiful. We had a reservation for 6pm, they greeted us and gave us seating options. We decided to get seated in the backyard beer garden. Each table was separated with glass. This place is great for large groups.  Now coming to food , we ordered Meatballs , Burrata , and Margherita pizza. Everything was so good. Following the appetizers, we decided on Hanger Steak and Fusilli Bolognese. Both dishes came out on a timely manner. Steak was cooked to perfection. We decided to make the Fusilli to go , as we got so full. Portions are huge and definitely worth the price. There was still room for dessert, we went with Tiramisu. It was too good literally was gone in 4 spoonfuls.  Ambiance- 10/10 Service- 10/10 WiFi- Not Sure Happy Hour - Yes I Believe Parking - Street Outdoor Dining - Yes Mask Mask - All Employees were following the CDC Guidelines

Really cool indoor, loved the garden dining. So romantic when it gets dark, loved the italian food but the secondo menue ( fish and steak) were just average. They do not currently have a coffee/ desert menue . Shortstaffed
Great drinks, ambience and service!

I went here on a Friday night and enjoyed the great rooftop space, beers, pizza, and calamari. First, the pizza was absolutely delicious, second they use a QR scan ordering system which makes it easy to order food/drinks without risk of menus not being sanitized.  The beers were top notch, I wish there was a larger draft selection but they have fantastic cans.  This is a great place to go even if just for the pizza.
Good place fast service via website menus. < sit down service quick, no breeze in the back session)
Quarantine rooftop bar on Fridays and Saturdays, but I missed it as I came on a Sunday. Still, the food was good, and as far as sidewalk cafe dining in NYC goes, it had good atmosphere
Orecchiette with sausage & broccoli rabe was good but a bit too salty. Less pesto would make it more palatable. Large portion a plus.

Lovely place with great ambience. Simple Italian fare that is dependable but doesn’t blow your socks off. You pay more for the scenery than you do for the food. Good laugh non the less. Food sat like a rock inside me after though. Probs shouldn’t of had risotto balls, pizza, and pasta. Thank god I live alone cause fireworks weren’t the only things popping off that night.

We made a reservation by phone at 7;30, when we arrived they didn’t find our reservation and we didn’t get sit, we had reservation notification and confirmation on phone, but manager didn’t sit us anyway. Then we made a reservation with him, at 8:00 and when we back, we still didn’t get our table and they said we gonna call you whenever we will have a table available even though they had 3-4 available tables. It wasn’t even wait outside to say there were busy. We got the table eventually with very rude hostess asking “ Do you need table or not?” Server was very nice though, but management is very poor.
Made reservation twice, never get a table! Hostess was really rude! I’m never coming back!
Huge inside, gorgeously decorated. Really yummy Italian food, good for groups and work parties.
Good food, nice atmosphere and friendly service.
Service and food are TOP-NOTCH
I've been at this venue a couple of times and I have to admit they have the best wings in the five boroughs! The food, ambience and service are outstanding.
Racist manager rudely kicked my friends out of the restaurant and threatened to call the police without providing a reason when asked multiple times.
Great environment and ambiance, bartenders and waiters are amazing
Service was great. Calamari was yummy. Good brick oven pizza.
Nice space , good drinks, good vibe
Great atmosphere, food and drinks.  Very reasonable.   Great time had by all.
Everything was great! Food, wine, cocktails, staff, venue, and price amazing. I probably wont cook this summer and just come here everyday!!!
Food was OK. Service was also shaky. We had to keep asking for the server to come to our table for drinks, food, and to pay. Otherwise the wine was good!
Came here just for drinks. Fun vibe in the back. Would definitely come back.
Great beer selection. Good cocktails. Calamari is not bad. 👍👍👍👍
large place with a cool atmosphere, love the indoor tree situation
Order the ribs!
all the food was FIRE
Literally everything we ordered was delicious! We went as a big group and the service was fantastic!

This place has incredible service, was here for a low-key engagement party at a table of about 20 people and the wait staff was attentive and quick with the many drinks and plates we ordered. Beautiful venue as well!
Very cute locale. Went for brunch and was satisfied—nothing impressive. Our 2 hour bottomless mimosas was cut 20 minutes early though which was disappointing.
Great decor and solid food options. Perfect for large groups looking to dine out
Came in winter. Had a nice outdoor patio vibe even though it was indoors. Great for larger groups
good place for group dining.

The Ainslie has become a regular weekend dinner spot for us. We have never had anything less than delicious there. Alex has been our server several times and he is simply the best! Attentive, informed, and so incredibly nice. He even comes over to say hi to my husband and I when he’s not our waiter. We love it there and also like that the menu is always changing while still keeping the best staples on the menu week over week.
Good Italian
Good food, good service, boisterous spot with a lively crowd. Hip music and bar. Good for groups and just drinks too.
Great pizza and friendly service
HUGE place with lots of drinks (like everything), cool brick interior, probably great for large groups.

Story about a New Year’s Eve at Ainslie; spoiler alert, not worth it. Reservation at 9:30pm for 11 persons, our waiter with a gigantic smile says that he’s going to take care of everything, confirms that everybody can have separate receipts and takes our drinks orders. The food was a fixed menu, pre-ordered days ago so it should go smoothly... Well, that it did not. All the food took sooooo long to come. We had to beg 4 times to have a refill for water; and our waiter was very annoyed when we asked for water again and where our food was because it took 30 minutes between salad and meal... But, because the tip is already included for large parties, no need to provide good service right? 11:45pm, still no entrees. 11:55pm, finally they arrived. Great midnight countdown with a chicken breast in my mouth. 12:05pm, free bubbly for countdown  arrives, yep, well after the countdown. I understand that on NYE, it’s going to be busy - but all other tables had been served and finished their meals. The menu was pre-ordered and very simple; meaning there was no reason it shouldn’t  have gone smoothly. Regarding the food, it was basic. The only positive aspect is the place itself that is very nice. And of course, we only had one receipt for the whole table. Thank you Ainslie, you’ll never see me again and I hope that anyone reading this review will go somewhere else. Bye!
Service is great food delicious Tequila shots water down so no five star for them
Ambiance is phenomenal. Food and prices, NO
I don't recommend driving here. Finding parking is what made is very late. It's great for large groups, they have everything else most other bars have. It's a decent place to go to.
Nice happy hour, great atmosphere. Great service.
They nailed every aspect of this place. I think I came here 4 times in one week before. Big win for Williamsburg.

WOW!!! What a amazing establishment!! Great vibes, delicious menu, classy atmosphere, breathtaking drinks, heartwarming desert and best of all FIRST CLASS SERVICE!! Ask for Alex and Zacc best service duo ever!!
Loved the food and drinks

Beautiful space, industrial feel with high ceilings, good lighting. Two main rooms with one on the front and one in back plus mezzanine lounge area, open at certain times. Well-run place with friendly, happy staff. Great place for happy hour. The pizza Amatriciana was excellent and spice. Spaghetti alla Vongole was delicious and Sicilian style with bread crumbs. Highly recommended. Sunday evening seemed quieter than Friday early evening. Reservations would be good for dinner.
Good food and service
Super chill atmosphere, with exquisite food! Great place for a date night, or large party.

This place is fantastic. We had the wings, a burrata, and the orecchiette pasta. Everything was delicious, some of the best food I've had in NYC. The beer selection was decent. The atmosphere was great and everyone was very friendly and helpful. We will most definitely be coming back here!
Loved the vibe and decor. The food and staff was really awesome also. I would definitely recommend trying this place out.
Beautiful decor with an amazing atmosphere. Awesome spot for a date night. The food was delicious! Highly recommend stopping by if you’re in the area.

Oh my heavenly goodness. You can’t go wrong here. Their prices are a bit high given you’re supposed to order multiple dishes and share amongst your group but they’re all fire. Specially,  their Margherita pizza is abnormally delicious for such a plain pizza. Service can sometimes be spotty but honestly, you’ll get your food and forget all about it. Also, VIBES?! This place is gorgeous. Inside or outside - it’s stunning.

The space itself is in a large gutted warehouse for an authentic Williamsburg vibe. The key takeaways from this restaurant were: The food is good. The dessert is excellent. The staff is friendly.  The service is fast, but almost too fast!!!  When I go to a restaurant I want to enjoy the experience not just the food. My only other complaint happened at the end of our meal. Our waitperson handed me the bill and immediately took out the credit card reader. He hovered over me while I entered the tip and signed the check. They offer automatic tip selections, the first one listed is 25%. The last option is 20%.  I am all for tipping restaurant staff well, but when I have someone staring down at me I feel uncomfortable.  I also don't like feeling that I am being cheap for not tipping 25%.  And now the boring stuff: The front of the space is dedicated to a restaurant and bar serving simple Italian fare. The menu offers a small, very affordable, selection of pastas, pizzas and mains. There is an impressive appetizer list which is great if you are having a drink at the bar. The alcohol menu is large and very affordable. There is a beer garden in the back and a private event space upstairs.  Order recommendations: calamari, burata, Greek salad, margherita pizza, branzini, tiramisu, marscapone.
OK restaurant, nice ambience, but nothing really super unique about the restaurant or the food (which was average/ a little disappointing considering the portions).
Divine.

Great food great company  Lovely host very common dating as busy as it was she still made sure she took good care of us And there was a lot of us Awesome music Definitely recommend this place will definitely go back again Clean organized and very nice people  They  Greeted you in And greeted you  when you Left

Twice here and not once had a bad experience. This place is pretty new but it's pack on a good day and semi pack on a bad. Highlight is the backyard and the lounge area that I haven't get a chance to see yet. Also the beer selection.  Let's start with happy hour 5 to 7 and with some pretty good selection of pizza and $1 meat ball. Most importantly is their pizza and pasta. I think their pizza is among the best. With just enough sauce and cheese, we have no problem finish them one after another. Beer is a bit "small". I wish they get a bigger glass as I can easily finish 2 glasses.  Service is wonderful. The waiter can be a bit busy time to time but always check back after a few minutes. We missed our last happy hour call cause he didn't come back for a long time thou. If you want to take advantage, order or call the waiter down. I have a feeling you can order with any waiter but you get a "main" waiter for you table.  Ambiance is better on the picture. The place is spacious but with all the people and stuff running around, it turns out not as spacious as on the yelp photo. Tell the host that you want a table in the back and yet have I gone to the upstairs yet. I need to go back !! Bye.

I give it 2 stars for the atmosphere.  The tables were high so we sat on stools that were so uncomfortable that I had to stand while having coffee. As far as the food goes, it was just so so. Definitely will not recommend this place.
Incredible atmosphere and good food. Since it’s brand new, the service was a little difficult to nail down, but food came incredibly fast after ordering. Will be going back!
Great new spot.  It’s not really a beer garden, rather an upscale casual restaurant. Plenty of excellent craft cocktails. The food was good,  reasonable,  but the service even better.
Phenomenal space, great food, terrific service.

Space is lovely, but some of the worst Italian food i’ve encountered in all of NY.  crispy artichokes were greasy and inedible. Pasta was undercooked and tasteless and in watery butter sauce with chunks of raw garlic and half cooked pancetta. house made ravioli were gritty, the chard inside was tough to chew, the butter sauce was over powering and over salted. the pizza was acceptable but only in comparison to the other dishes. zucchini bruschetta was the best part of the meal and it was three thin slices of zucchini on a thick layer of ricotta.  service was okay, it was a busy night with a lot of patrons but was good enough. seriously though, the food was heinous.
Mixed drink was not good, food looked great and space was awesome. 3.5 stars, will go back to eat with a crew.
Food is so-so and the atmosphere is LOUD.
Beautiful place, delicious food. Service could be a little slower so we can enjoy a beautiful night
Beautiful locations, delicious selection of beers and cocktails. Very friendly staff!! Definitely will go back!
Wings and ribs are awesome.

Visited this place on Saturday. Staff was extremely friendly, especially the gentleman that served us food and drink (guy with a beard that flew out on Sunday) the food is really well prepared. Pizza and wings are the way to go. The decor very chill and I got nothing but good vibes. I will definitely be visiting again.
They ran out of the crispy artichoke-  but had these great foods

I think as time goes this place will settle in and become more of a local spot. As my first experience, the overall look is on point, the decor is industrial modern and done well. The only issue I had was they ran out of every beer I asked for and instead of telling me what they have, I was left to guess what beer they did have on tap. Overall lots of potential and excited to see where they go.

What a great new addition to the neighborhood.  The food is top notch.  Try the salt and pepper ribs, wings, pizzas and orecchiette with sausage and broccoli rabe or the papardelle with pork ragu.  The space itself is gorgeous. The back patio is amazing. Wine selection is solid.   Great place.
Really cool interior, friendly and attentive service, and tasty food and drinks. Looking forward to coming back to try more items on the menu.
